Throughout the book, Kahneman invites readers to reflect on their own thinking patterns and biases. He provides practical insights into how to recognize and mitigate these biases, allowing for more deliberate and informed decision-making. By understanding the limitations of our cognitive processes, readers can make wiser choices and improve their overall decision-making abilities.

